## ✅ FIXED! Chart Now Shows ONLY Requested Time Range!

The problem was the chart was showing **ALL CACHED DATA** (1441 candles from 6 days ago) instead of just the requested hour.

### What I Fixed:

1. **Added Data Filtering** - Now filters fetched data to ONLY include candles within the requested time range
2. **Removed fitContent()** - This was making the chart show all data regardless of what we asked for
3. **Force Correct Time Range** - Now uses `visibleStartTime` and `alignedNow` (the calculated 1-hour range) instead of the full data range
4. **Applied to Both Initial Load and Reload** - Fixed in both functions

### The Fix:
```javascript
// Filter data to only what we need
const filteredData = data.filter(candle => 
  candle.time >= visibleStartTime && candle.time <= alignedNow
);

// Force the exact range we want
chart.timeScale().setVisibleRange({
  from: visibleStartTime as Time,
  to: alignedNow as Time
});
```

Now when you select **1H**, it will show exactly **60 candles** of the last hour, not 1400+ candles from the entire cache!

The date range debug will also show matching expected and actual values.

